1.0.1 Missing Data Rule

  • For scales with 10 or more items, a composite score (average/total) is computed for each participant that have less than 20% of the items from that measure missing

  • For scales with 7 to 9 items, a composite score (average/total) is computed for each participant that have less than 30% of the items from that measure missing

  • For scales with 3 to 6 items, a composite score (average/total) is computed for each participant that have less than 33% of the items from that measure missing

  • For scales with only 2 items, composite scores (average/total) are calculated on a case by case basis

2.1 Brief Symptom Inventory (BSI)

2.1.1 BSI Description

The BSI is used to assess … INSERT TEXT DESCRIPTION ABOUT BSI MEASURE

For the present study, 19 items from the BSI were collected in order to calculate the Somatization, Anxiety, and Depression subscales.

Item numbers in this dataset may not match original item numbers from the BSI exactly (?)

No items need to be reverse scored. Higher scores indicate more severe mental health symptoms.

The missing data rule was not applied since there is no missing data among BSI variables.

Reference: Derogatis and Melisaratos (1983); DOI

2.1.2 BSI Variables

2.1.2.1 Value Labels

All BSI variables have the same response options

0 1 2 3 4
Not at all A little bit Moderately Quite a bit Very much

2.2 Center for Epidemiologic Studies Depression Scale (CES-D)

2.2.1 CES-D Description

The CES-D is used to assess … INSERT TEXT DESCRIPTION ABOUT CES-D MEASURE

All 20 items from the CES-D were collected. Two subscales are included as variables, positive affect and depressive symptoms. Four items (c4, c8, c12, and c16) are/should be reverse scored which is noted in the variable table below. Higher scores indicate the presence of more symptoms.

Four additional variables (c21-c24) were included in this section to assess suicidality. Variables c22 and c23 are only applicable if participants responded “Yes” to c21.

The missing data rule was not applied since all participants had less than 20% missing data. Missing data for each variable is presented in the summary information below.

Reference: Radloff (1977); DOI

  • Additional References:

    • Cutoff Information: Henry, Grant, and Cropsey (2018); DOI

    • Items for Potential Subscales: Canady, Stommel, and Holzman (2009); DOI

2.2.2 CES-D Variables

2.2.2.1 Value Labels

All CES-D survey items (c1-c20) have the same response options

0 1 2 3
Rarely or none of the time Some or a little of the time Occasionally or a moderate amount of time Most or all of the time

Additional variables on suicidality (c21-c24) share the same response options

0 1 2
No Yes Declined to Answer

2.2.2.2 Survey Items

All CES-D survey items are presented in the following table

Variable Description Notes
c1 During the past week, I was bothered by things that usually don’t bother me
c2 I did not feel like eating; my appetite was poor
c3 I felt that I could not shake off the blues even with help from my family or friends
c4 During the past week, I felt that I was just as good as other people This item should be reverse scored. c4_r is reverse scored
c5 I had trouble keeping my mind on what I was doing.
c6 I felt depressed
c7 During the past week, I felt that everything I did was an effort
c8 I felt hopeful about the future This item should be reverse scored. c8_r is reverse scored
c9 I thought my life had been a failure
c10 During the past week, I felt fearful
c11 My sleep was restless
c12 I was happy This item should be reverse scored. c12_r is reverse scored
c13 During the past week, I talked less than usual
c14 I felt lonely
c15 People were unfriendly
c16 During the past week, I enjoyed life This item should be reverse scored. c16_r is reverse scored
c17 I had crying spells
c18 I felt sad
c19 During the past week, I felt that people disliked me
c20 I could not “get going”
c21

In the past 6 months, have you ever thought about killing yourself?

Assessor Note: Read the answer options as the choices have changed.
c22 In the past 6 months, have you thought often about killing yourself? Skipped if c21 = No
c23 In the past 6 months, did you have a plan for killing yourself? Skipped if c21 = No
c24 In the past 6 months, have you tried to kill yourself?
